race.comment: LEXY ROSE (9) shed the maiden tag in town at the latest effort over this trip and will have come on with that win now in the locker. Gets in well at the weights with the 1.5kg claim and should be right there at the business end. WELLY (6) has a win and a second from three spins around this circuit and has been racing very consistently of late. Solid top-three prospects. AMAHNI'S GIRL (7) has hit the top-five at her past six starts and is usually thereabouts. One for the exotics. CAVARETTA (8) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on. MAD ANA (10) wasn't beaten far on resuming. Fitter and was racing consistently through her last campaign.
